subject: p12658584
History: Atypical chest pain. Evaluate for consolidation, fluid overload, or other cause of chest pain.
Findings: There is central pulmonary vascular congestion with moderate pulmonary edema. The chronicity of these findings is unknown due to the lack of comparison studies. There is no focal consolidation, pneumothorax, or pleural effusion.
Impression: Congestive heart failure, likely acute. Acute myocardial infarction should be ruled out as the cause of failure given patients young age and acuity of presentation. The patient was transferred to the emergency department for further evaluation. Dr. In the ED was contacted by Dr. Telephone on at 16:45.
